HEADWORD: Day-laborer
<hw>Day"-la`bor*er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>One who works
by the day; -- usually applied to a farm laborer, or to a workman who
does not work at any particular trade.</def>
<rj><au>Goldsmith.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

